Spanish Stocks: Ferrovial, Abertis, Solaria, Amper Shares Move

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-02-23T09:41:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/spanish-stocks-ferrovial-abertis-solaria-amper-shares-move.html
Spainâ€™s  IBEX 35 index  fell for a
fourth day, losing 31.8, or 0.3 percent, to 10,670.1 as of 10:40
a.m. in Madrid. The Madrid Stock Exchange General Index declined
1 percent.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Spanish market. Symbols are in parentheses after company names.    Abertis Infraestructuras SA  (ABE SM) climbed 1.7 percent to
14.65 euros, snapping three days of losses. The Spanish company
said it may group its five units into two companies, Abertis
Infraestructuras and Saba Infraestructuras. Abertis may group
its highways, telecommunications and airport divisions into
Abertis Infraestructuras and its parking and logistics parks
into Saba.    Amper SA  (AMP SM) advanced for a second day, gaining 2.9
percent to 3.88 euros. The Spanish defense contractor said it
won an order worth more than 90 million euros ($123 million)
from the United Arab Emirates.    Ferrovial SA  (FER SM) rose for a second day, adding 1
percent to 8.79 euros. The manager of highways and airports
posted a full-year profit of 2.16 billion euros, compared with a
loss of 73.5 million euros a year.    Solaria Energia y Medio Ambiente SA  (SLR SM) soared 8.4
percent to 1.75 euros, breaking four days of losses. The Spanish
solar-cell manufacturer said full-year profit jumped to 6.5
million euros from 2.5 million euros a year earlier. Sales
climbed 81 percent to 161.3 million euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
